@startuml

box "Male Mobile" #e4fcfa
    participant "Horizontal Sub-system" as MaleHorizontalSubsystem
    participant "Drive Sub-system" as MaleDriveSubsystem
    participant "Main System" as MaleSystem
end box

' The system from which the male hangs, it rotates and oscillates
' It will stop when the Male with the greatest drive requests it
box "Beam" #e6fcc1
    participant "Beam Main System" as Beam
end box

box "Environment" #fcf6c1
    participant "Environment" as Environment
end box

box #f9c6e8
    Actor "Female or Human" as Actor
end box

' Agent's behavior based on state managed by Male System
loop System Running

    MaleSystem -> MaleDriveSubsystem : Get Drive State 
    MaleDriveSubsystem -> MaleSystem : Drive State 
    MaleSystem -> MaleDriveSubsystem : Get Drive Values
    MaleDriveSubsystem -> MaleSystem : Drive Values

    MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Display Drive State
    MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Display Drives

    alt Male System State = Satisfaction Search
        MaleSystem -> MaleHorizontalSubsystem : Search [Release]
        MaleSystem -> Beam : Search [Release]
        MaleSystem -> Environment : Intermittent Signal This Satisfaction Search and ID
        Environment -> Actor : Intermittent Signal This Satisfaction Search and ID
        MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Listen for Response
        Actor --> Environment : Identifying Signal
        Environment --> MaleSystem : Identifying Signal

        alt Response = This Satisfaction Search
            MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : State = Engaging a Partner
            MaleSystem -> MaleHorizontalSubsystem : Stop
            MaleSystem -> Beam : Stop
            loop Engaging Partner
                MaleSystem -> Environment : Energetic Beam
                Environment -> Actor : Energetic Beam
                Actor --> Environment : Light
                Environment --> MaleSystem : Light
                MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Sense Light
                alt Light Sensed > Threshold
                    MaleSystem -> Environment : Reinforcement Signal
                    Environment -> Actor : Reinforcement Signal
                    MaleSystem -> MaleDriveSubsystem : Decrement Drive
                    MaleSystem -> MaleDriveSubsystem : Get Drive State 
                    MaleDriveSubsystem -> MaleSystem : Drive State 
                    MaleSystem -> MaleDriveSubsystem : Get Drive Values
                    MaleDriveSubsystem -> MaleSystem : Drive Values
                    MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Display Drive State
                    MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Display Drives
                    alt Drive State = Satisfied and Indifferent
                        MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Satisfaction Display
                        MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : State = Satisfied and Indifferent
                    else Drive State = This Satisfaction Search
                        MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Continue Engaging Partner
                    else Drive State = Either O or P Satisfaction Search
                        MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : Continue Engaging Partner
                    else Drive State = Other Satisfaction Search
                        MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : State = Satisfaction Search
                    end
                else Timeout
                    MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : State = Satisfaction Search
                end
            end
        else Response Timeout
            MaleSystem -> MaleSystem : State = Satisfaction Search
        end
    else Male System State = Satisfied and Indifferent
        MaleSystem -> MaleHorizontalSubsystem : Stop
        MaleSystem -> Beam : Satisfied and Indifferent [Release]
    end
end

legend right
  <b>As-built annotations (2026-07-18):</b>
  - Signal media: Intermittent Signal = light (Male NeoPixel ring, 40-segment binary word);
    Identifying + Reinforcement Signals = sound (audio tones).
  - "Decrement Drive" is a windowed reinforcement tally (80-sample window, timer_reinforce;
    sum > trigger -> decrement = sum x 10), not a single decrement per reflection.
  - The three Beam requests (Search[Release] / Stop / Satisfied[Release]) collapse to one bit
    (beamStopRequest) in the engine - no consumer branched on the three spellings.
  Source: src/simulation/behavior/state-machine-male.ts, beam-arbitrator.ts.
endlegend

@enduml